BUG: Taps don't fire for terminal invocations

When an event is called at the END of a pipeline (terminal position),
taps don't fire because there's no "destination" to transition to.

Expected: Tap should fire when event completes, even as terminal
Actual: Tap doesn't fire

This breaks the promise that ~tap(event -> *) observes ALL transitions
from that event, including when it's the last thing in a flow.

Acceptance criteria:
- ~tap(print.ln -> *) fires even when print.ln is terminal
- No performance regression for non-tapped terminal events
